# Project scope (MVP+)

## Product

Operational logistics dashboard: shipments, tracking checkpoints, managers, partners/clients, finance, export, Telegram settings, dashboard analytics.

## Stack

| Layer | Tech |
|-------|------|
| Frontend | React + Vite (`src/`) |
| Backend | Laravel API (`backend/`) |
| Local DB | SQLite |
| Production DB | PostgreSQL on Render |
| Hosting | Vercel (frontend), Render (backend) |

## Preserve unless task says otherwise

- Dashboard-style UI; simple, modern, Russian labels.
- Existing navigation and page structure in `src/`.
- API JSON response shapes and field naming (camelCase in JSON).

## Out of scope (unless task explicitly requests)

- Auth, JWT, roles, permissions (Users page is post-MVP).
- Payment gateways, invoicing integrations beyond current finance UI.
- Real Telegram message sending (settings UI only).
- Full redesign, new theme, parallel UI trees (`reference/`, `client-logistics-ui/`).
- Copying UI to another repo.

## Approach

- Incremental, task-scoped diffs.
- Feature branches → local QA → PR → merge → deploy → production QA.
- Mock data in `src/data/` only when API is not configured; never mask failures when `VITE_API_BASE_URL` is set.

See `docs/MVP_PLUS_SCOPE.md`, `docs/AI_WORKFLOW.md`, `.cursor/README.md`.
